# Cursor Rules for Unraid Integration

## Project Structure
- Custom component follows Home Assistant integration structure
- Documentation uses MkDocs with Material theme
- Memory Bank contains project documentation

## Coding Patterns
- Follow Home Assistant coding standards
- Use asynchronous patterns with async/await
- Use coordinator pattern for data updates
- Implement proper error handling

## Documentation Patterns
- Use markdown for all documentation
- Follow MkDocs structure with navigation
- Include admonitions for important notes
- Document all services and entities

## File Organization
- Keep related functionality in same modules
- Use const.py for constants
- Use helpers.py for shared utility functions
- Place translations in translations directory

## Project Workflow
- Update Memory Bank when making significant changes
- Test all changes with actual Unraid server when possible
- Document all user-facing features
- Follow Home Assistant integration quality guidelines

## User Experience Focus
- Provide clear error messages
- Implement repair flows for common issues
- Make configuration process intuitive
- Document common use cases

## Development Practices
- Use consistent code formatting
- Write descriptive commit messages
- Update documentation when changing functionality
- Test with different Unraid configurations

## Memory Bank Maintenance
- Keep activeContext.md and progress.md updated
- Document all technical decisions
- Capture system architecture changes
- Track project progress 